---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Google Business Profile: optimize your listing | visibilite-locale.online"
  description="Complete guide to optimizing your Google Business Profile. Appear in the local pack and attract more customers."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
      <nav class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <a href="/en/" class="hover:text-blue-600">Home</a> &rsaquo;
        <a href="/en/guide-seo-local" class="hover:text-blue-600">Local SEO Guide</a> &rsaquo;
        <span class="text-gray-900">Google Business Profile</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">Google Business Profile</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Optimize your Google Business Profile listing to appear in the local pack and attract more customers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 prose">
      <h2>Why Google Business Profile matters</h2>
      <p>
        Google Business Profile (formerly Google My Business) is the cornerstone of local SEO. Your listing appears directly in search results and on Google Maps when potential customers search for your products or services nearby.
      </p>

      <h2>Create and claim your listing</h2>
      <p>
        The first step is to create or claim your listing on business.google.com. Make sure your business doesn't already have an existing listing to avoid duplicates.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Check for existing listings by searching your business name on Google Maps</li>
        <li>If a listing exists, claim it via the "Claim this business" button</li>
        <li>Complete verification by mail, phone, or email</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Optimize essential information</h2>
      <p>
        A complete and accurate listing improves your local ranking. Key elements to fill in carefully:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Business name</strong>: use your exact official name, without added keywords</li>
        <li><strong>Address</strong>: complete physical address consistent with your website</li>
        <li><strong>Phone number</strong>: preferably a local number</li>
        <li><strong>Primary category</strong>: choose the most specific category possible</li>
        <li><strong>Business hours</strong>: update regularly, including holidays</li>
        <li><strong>Website</strong>: link to your site or a local landing page</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Photos and visual content</h2>
      <p>
        Listings with photos receive 42% more direction requests. Add quality photos showing your business, products, team, and interior.
      </p>

      <h2>Google Posts</h2>
      <p>
        Use posts to share news, special offers, and events. Posts remain visible for 7 days and show Google that your listing is active.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Related articles</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 text-blue-700">
          <li><a href="/en/blog/en-attributs-gbp/">Google Business Profile Attributes: Which to Enable and Why</a></li>
          <li><a href="/en/blog/en-multi-etablissements-gbp/">Managing Multiple GBP Listings</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
